Hey #Toronto! I’m partnering with @quell.now for a special keynote panel session on race, identity and reality TV. 

I’ll be alongside @chefericak, Season 9 Top Chef Canada winner, @ellejays_ , Master Chef Canada two-time alumni and moderator @azaleazoe. We’ll chat about our personal winning strategies and how we have navigated the game with two (or more) strikes already against us. We’ll be part of the Unblock unconference Opening Networking Party at @barordecai on March 28 😊

The inaugural Unblock unconference focuses on diversity, equity and inclusion in the food, drink and hospitality industries. I’m honoured to join a great line-up of expert and thought leaders who are sharing their lived experiences to inspire sustainable change and contribute to a more open, diverse and inclusive industry. 
 
On March 28-29, Unblock will include three marquee events, 30+ speakers – all from 100% underrepresented groups, 25+ featured small businesses, and four learning streams. 
 
Sessions and tickets are limited, so get yours today at www.unblockto.com or the link in my bio

Those passions you had when you were young, even if they seemed insignificant, you questioned whether you were good enough or were told “no,” can come back around!

#sponsored A personal update: I’m freezing my eggs.

… and I’m taking you on the journey. I’ve always dreamed of having children and being a mom. I also have so many other dreams I’m still chasing. I made the choice to freeze my eggs to give myself more options for making all of my dreams come true.

I’ve partnered with @evolve_egg_freeze to share my egg freezing journey. EVOLVE is Canada’s first and only egg freezing clinic. It’s my way to pay it forward and thank all of the women and people with uteruses in my life who have shared their journeys with me.

Stay tuned because I’m documenting the journey on Instagram and tiktok.

My life has changed a ton over the last few years - yes, even pre reality TV! There are definitely moments when I feel like I’m flying high. There are tons of moments when I hope I’m on the right path, doing the right thing. I always choose doing what’s true to me and having faith that it’ll work out … even if people don’t understand it 🥳.

I love to reflect on a younger version of Erika who wanted to do and experience so many things. She didn’t realize at the time that anything is possible. Now I know and I’m going for it. Even though moving forward can be filled with uncertainty, I gotta remember every step I take now is a past Erika’s dream come true 🤗

What will my 34th year bring? 🎉

I remember back in the day I thought by this age I’d “have it together.” What does it even mean to have it together? Stable career? A family?

A couple years ago I was doing the right things on paper (I think). Yet, when I thought about what I wanted for the future I would draw a blank. Do I keep working my job and become a vice president with a good retirement plan or something?

The last year was filled with new experiences. I took risks and showed different sides of myself. I spent more time with people who have the same love for all of life’s possibilities. I pursued passions. I leaned into change, hard decisions and moments of joy. Ultimately, I felt like me.

How does it feel to think about the future now? Exciting. I don’t need to “have it together.” Instead, I’m more confident than ever that I can handle the ebbs and flows of life in a way that’s authentically me.

Thank you to my previous chapter 🙏🏽

Finally packed up the rest of my stuff from my old place. It’s hard to capture 10 years of growth in just 21 photos. When I moved into my old place, I was in my early 20s, new-ish to Toronto, unsure of my place and who I wanted to be in the world. I had straight across bangs and long, natural coloured hair and I kept it because other people liked it. Over the last decade I’d consistently challenge myself to try something out of my comfort zone. The baby steps (like getting a gym membership), turned into bigger steps (like becoming a seasoned solo traveller and leaving my career) and then transformed into big leaps (like playing a game on TV). I close that chapter thankful for a place that kept me safe and enabled me to grow into a brave, confident, flawed-yet-self-accepting, purple-haired woman who still doesn’t understand the world but understands herself more profoundly than before. Thank you old place 🏢❤️

Now it’s time to grow in my new chapter ✨

Sometimes the scary moments are the ones you learn from, right?

Got to spend the weekend speaking to brave young girls about my Exile Island experience. I remember being a kid and the feeling of being left out. It was rewarding to share what that experience taught me about moving through nerves and thinking positively when you feel isolated. Who knew that my #Survivor ~nightmare~ ended up being a source of connection that allows me to help others to build their confidence? ❤️

Thank you @workitjanet for including me in your WORK IT Girl programming 💖

After years of work I did a chin up! 💪🏽

It’s been my goal for YEARS to do an unassisted chin up. 

I never played sports growing up. When I became an adult and moved to Toronto I fell in love with working out. I accomplished things I’m so proud of (half marathons, amateur boxing bouts, etc). Though tbh a lot of my fitness goals were about achieving a certain ~look~ that in hindsight was probably not realistically attainable.

When I started strength training, I wanted to work towards feeling strong. So, I set a goal to do a chin up. 

I spent months strengthening all of the muscles I needed to make it happen. I got close … and then the pandemmy happened and threw off my plans. Then I starved on an island on TV, lost all of my muscle and had to rebuild basically from scratch. But this fall, I finally reached my goal and pulled myself up on my own! 🥲

This journey taught me about persistence, accepting that the timing isn’t always what we have in mind and that’s okay, and overall, when I put my mind to it I’m a bad ass 😎🦄

Thank you @paul.hynes for your guidance, expertise and support in getting me to this goal. Time to work towards the next one 🚙🫷💨
